					"numinlets" : 1,
					"numoutlets" : 0,
					"patching_rect" : [ 474.0, 403.0, 193.0, 123.0 ],
					"text" : "Solution 3: The sw abstraction (included with the examples) solves the problem by temporarily disconnecting local reception while sending. This is simpler, since the working part of the patch can be connected directly to the control element.",
					"textcolor" : [ 0.501961, 0.501961, 0.501961, 1.0 ]
				}

			}
, 			{
				"box" : 				{
					"fontname" : "Arial",
					"fontsize" : 13.0,
					"frgb" : 0.0,
					"id" : "obj-30",
					"linecount" : 8,
					"maxclass" : "comment",
					"numinlets" : 1,
					"numoutlets" : 0,
					"patching_rect" : [ 474.0, 229.0, 190.0, 123.0 ],
					"text" : "Solution 2: The var abstraction (included with the examples) solves the problem by using a \"set\" message to control the local controller, and a separate outlet to control the part of the patch that is actually doing something useful.",
					"textcolor" : [ 0.501961, 0.501961, 0.501961, 1.0 ]
				}

			}
, 			{
				"box" : 				{
					"fontname" : "Arial",
					"fontsize" : 13.0,
					"frgb" : 0.0,
					"id" : "obj-29",
					"linecount" : 8,
					"maxclass" : "comment",
					"numinlets" : 1,
					"numoutlets" : 0,
					"patching_rect" : [ 474.0, 52.0, 195.0, 123.0 ],
					"text" : "Solution 1: The value object works much like a send-receive pair, except that the message is strored (set) rather than sent immediately. Thus there is no feedback loop. To output the value, send a \"bang\" message to the object to be controlled.",
					"textcolor" : [ 0.501961, 0.501961, 0.501961, 1.0 ]
				}

			}
, 			{
				"box" : 				{
					"fontname" : "Arial",
					"fontsize" : 13.0,
					"frgb" : 0.0,
					"id" : "obj-27",
					"linecount" : 6,
					"maxclass" : "comment",
					"numinlets" : 1,
					"numoutlets" : 0,
					"patching_rect" : [ 21.0, 291.0, 400.0, 94.0 ],
					"text" : "Unfortunately, connecting sends and receives in both directions does not work. Touching either dial object below will immediately cause a feedback loop. To resume normal operation, close the yellow stack overflow notification in this window or choose \"Resume\" from the Edit menu. Typically, one resumes after eliminating the loop.",
					"textcolor" : [ 0.501961, 0.501961, 0.501961, 1.0 ]
				}

			}
, 			{
				"box" : 				{
					"fontname" : "Arial",
